<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I have been trying to create custom routes by using the following syntax (copy and paste from the online docs):-</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
routes.news.type = "My_Route"
routes.news.route = "news"
routes.news.defaults.controller = "news"
routes.news.defaults.action = "list"
</code></pre>

<p>My class 'My_Route' extends Zend_Controller_Router_Route. However, the 'getInstance' method in Zend_Controller_Router_Route uses the syntax new self(args) to return an instance. Because of PHP's late static binding limitations, this returns Zend_Controller_Router_Route rather than My_Route.</p>

    </div>
